  <bodyText><![CDATA[<h2><img src="/media/13107199/inghams-service-resort-rep-800x200.jpg" alt="InghamsPayment" data-udi="umb://media/b3392e723d5645c1957a864c565dc6c2" /></h2>
<h2>Payment methods - Inghams holiday bookings</h2>
<p>Chose the best way to pay for your next Inghams holidays that suits you best - whether its payment a low deposit to secure your booking or setting up a direct debit payment plan to spread the cost. </p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="#directdebit" data-anchor="#directdebit">Direct debit</a> - <a href="#lovwdeposit" data-anchor="#lowdeposit">Low deposit</a></p>
<div class="row">
<div id="directdebit" class="col-xs-12 col-md-12">
<div class="c-card c-card--generic c-card--generic-shadow">
<h3 style="text-align: center;">Direct Debits</h3>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img style="width: 100px; height: 100px;" src="/media/13109256/direct-debit-jpeg-100x100.jpg?width=100&amp;height=100" alt="DirectDebits" data-udi="umb://media/ef8feacecc3545fe8a3c16e7081bd335" /></p>
<p><strong>Secure, simple, and stress-free payments with Trustly</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Hassle-free payments: Trustly is the button you tap at checkout to pay directly from your online bank account - no cards needed, no stress involved.</li>
<li>Secure and reliable: As an authorised and regulated service by the UK Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), Trustly guarantees peace of mind with every transaction.</li>
<li>Simple and convenient: It’s quick, easy, and takes care of itself - giving you more time to focus on planning your experience.</li>
<li>Spread the cost with ease</li>
</ul>
<p>Planning your next Inghams holiday has never been easier - With Trustly’s zero fees and interest-free payments, you can spread the cost of your holiday into manageable monthly payments, helping you stay on budget without a large upfront bill.</p>
<p>View Direct debit Terms and Conditions <a data-udi="umb://document/af6732218b174bf898c6ed30f1d320ec" href="/{localLink:umb://document/af6732218b174bf898c6ed30f1d320ec}" title="Booking Conditions">here</a></p>
<h3>Direct debit FAQ's</h3>
<p><strong>Can I book an Inghams holiday without paying a deposit?</strong><br />You sure can! When you book a new Inghams holiday and choose to pay by direct debit through our trusted partner, Trustly, there’s no need to pay a deposit upfront. It’s that easy!<br /><br /><strong>What is Trustly?</strong><br />At Inghams, we believe your holiday should be all about making memories, not worrying about payments. That’s why we’ve partnered with Trustly - a secure and trusted payment solution that makes it easier to spread the cost of your holiday. Trustly isn’t an app - it’s simply a button you tap at checkout to pay directly from your online bank account. No cards needed, no hassle involved. Plus, with Trustly being authorised and regulated by the UK Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), you can rest easy knowing every transaction is safe and secure. Now you can focus on the exciting stuff—like what to pack for your adventure! <br /><br /><strong>How do Trustly direct debits work?</strong><br />Trustly direct debits make it easy to spread the cost of your holiday - with no payment fees and no interest to worry about. This option is available for new customers booking holidays that are more than 18 weeks away, as we’ll need to collect at least two direct debit payments before your final balance is due (10 weeks before your departure).<br />Please note that existing bookings aren’t eligible for direct debit payments, but it’s a great option for planning ahead with a new holiday.<br /><br /><strong>What are the benefits of paying by direct debit?</strong><br />Paying by direct debit is secure, guaranteed, and designed to give you peace of mind. It’s a simpler, more convenient way to spread the cost of your holiday, making budgeting easier and avoiding the stress of paying a large bill all at once. Plus, with no payment fees or interest, it’s a hassle-free, reliable option that lets you focus on looking forward to your trip!<br /><br /><strong>How can I set up a direct debit?</strong><br />Setting up a direct debit is easy! You can do it through our website when you book your holiday, as long as your departure is more than 18 weeks away. This gives us enough time to collect at least two payments before the full balance is due, which is 10 weeks before your departure. Once your direct debit is set up, we’ll send you a confirmation email with the payment amounts and due dates. Payments will be taken on either the 1st or 15th of each month, depending on when you book, and we’re not able to offer a choice of dates. Please note, that the bank account used for direct debit must be in the name of the lead passenger on the booking.<br /><br /><strong>Will there be any changes to my direct debit?</strong><br />If you need to make changes to your booking that affect the price, you'll simply need to settle any extra costs or fees at the time of the change. If your changes reduce the cost of your holiday, we’ll update your direct debit schedule, and your monthly payments will be adjusted accordingly. And don’t worry, if there are any changes to the amount, date, or frequency of your payments, we’ll give you a heads-up at least 3 working days before we take any payment from your account, unless we’ve agreed something different.<br /><br /><strong>What happens if I need to cancel my holiday?</strong><br />We get it - plans change! If you need to cancel your booking or can’t travel, our usual cancellation charges will apply, as outlined in 1.4(b). If you haven’t paid enough through direct debits to cover the cost at the time of cancellation, we’ll ask you to pay the remaining balance. Or, if you’ve already paid more than what’s due, we’ll refund the difference to you.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="row">
<div id="lowdeposit" class="col-xs-12 col-md-12">
<div class="c-card c-card--generic c-card--generic-shadow">
<h3 style="text-align: center;"><br />Deposits</h3>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img style="width: 100px; height: 100px;" src="/media/13105954/low-deposit-100x100.jpg?width=100&amp;height=100" alt="LowDeposit" data-udi="umb://media/19f1279eb86a47bbb7b6af6403fdd360" /></p>
<p><strong>We offer a low deposit option</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Reserve your holiday for just £150 per person.</li>
<li>Your final balance will be due 10 weeks before departure.</li>
<li>For some dates we might need to increase the deposit a little to secure your choice of flights.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
